These Holiday Oreo Brownies are always a huge hit!  They take 5 minutes prep time and are ooey gooey and so delicious.  Serve them at your holiday party or put them in a cute bag or tin for neighbor gifts!  Recipe below and also on my blog link in bio! 

HOLIDAY  OREO  BROWNIES
1 box brownie mix (I love Duncan Hines Fudgey and Chewy Mix)
2 eggs
3 tablespoons water
2/3 cup oil
1 package double stuff oreos
red and green sprinkles

Mix the brownies according to the box. In a greased baking dish spread half of the brownis mixture. Take the lids off the Oreos and layer then across the bottom layer of brownie bater. Drizzle the remaining half of brownie batter over the top. Bake 350 degrees about 25 minutes. I like mine really gooey in the middle so I cook less time than the box says. Remove and let cool. Cut into bite size pieces and sprinkle with red and green sprinkles.

Let’s make Creamy Baked Chicken.  This is a dish my mom used to make when I was growing up and it was an absolute favorite of mine.  She often served it when entertaining and it was always a huge hit! It’s only a handful of ingredients and so easy to make.  The chicken always cooks perfectly and is tender and moist and the creamy sauce is the best!  Recipe Below and also on my blog link in bio! #masoneats #bakedchicken #dinnerideas 

CREAMY BAKED CHICKEN
4 Chicken Breasts, boneless and skinless
1 can Cream Of Chicken Soup 
1/4 cup White Wine
10-12 slices Swiss Cheese
1 cup Herb Stuffing Mix
1/4 cup Butter

Arrange chicken breasts in a baking dish and season with salt and pepper.
Cover the chicken with slices of Swiss cheese (the original recipe says two slices per breast but I did 3 because I love cheese)
In a bowl stir together the cream of chicken soup and white wine. Pour this mixture over the cheese covered chicken.
Take the cup of herb stuffing mix and sprinkle over the top. Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350°F for 45 minutes

Let’s make Antipasto Balls 🤩
My sister sent me this recipe and I was like I have to make these!  So many of my favorite Charcuterie ingredients chopped and all Rolled into a bite size ball! You can make these ahead of time but I wouldn’t roll the nut mixture more than a day ahead of time.  I find it best if rolled before serving.  Optional to serve with a pretzel stick which I find makes it easier to pick them up!  Recipe below and on my blog link in bio!  #masoneats #appetizerideas #cheeseballs 

ANTIPASTO BALLS (original recipe from Carlsbad Cravings)
12 oz cream cheese a black and a half room temperature 
3 tablespoons sour cream 
1 cup freshly grated mozzarella 
1/4 cup grated Parmesan Cheese 
15 pieces salami diced 
1/4 cup pitted Kalamata olives dried and chopped 
1/4 cup red bell pepper diced 
1/4 cup sun dried tomatoes rinsed, dried and sliced 
1 teaspoon red wine vinegar 
2 tablespoons chopped chives
2 tablespoons fresh parsley 
2 tablespoons fresh basil 
1 teaspoon garlic powder
1 teaspoon onion powder 
1/2 teaspoon dried oregano
Salt and pepper 

Coating 
1/2 cup pecans or walnuts
1/2 cup pistachios
1 tablespoon parsley 
Chop all together and mix well

Mix all the cheese ball ingredients together well (not the nut mixture) and chill at least 30 minutes 
Use a mini cookie scooper to scoop mixture and roll into balls.  Coat each ball with the nut mixture.  Add a pretzel right before serving or it will become soggy!

Let’s make my favorite Cabbage Salad.  This is a recipe from my mom we used to eat often and it still remains one of my favorites!  It’s tangy, crunchy and so delicious.  Recipe below and will Also be posted on my blog (link in bio)! #masoneats #cabbagesalad 

CABBAGE  SALAD 
1 head green cabbage thinly sliced/shredded
2 packages soy ramen (break up the ramen and save the sauce packets) 
1 bunch green onions
1/2 cup sunflower seeds
1/2 cup sliced almonds 

DRESSING 
Save the two packets from the Ramen
1 cup olive oil 
4 tablespoons sugar 
6 tablespoons balsamic vinegar

Mix all the dressing ingredients together. You will need a fork or whisk to separate the sugar and blend it well.  Pour over the salad ingredients and toss all together.  This gets better the longer that it sits however I usually can never wait and eat it right away.  Enjoy!

My Loaded Greek Tortellini Pasta Salad is the BEST pasta salad.  It’s the perfect dish to take to a friend or family member and they can enjoy it for days!  It comes together quickly and has all my favorite Greek flavors and ingredients!  Always my mottos is the more toppings/ ingredients the better! Recipe below and also on my blog under the recipes tab link in bio! #masoneats #pastasalad 

LOADED  GREEK  TORTELLINI PASTA  SALAD
1 family size package cheese tortellini 
Garlic Expressions Dressing (or Italian Or Greek dressing)
1 cup cherry tomatoes halved 
2 baby cucumbers diced 
1/2 red onion diced 
1/3 cup halved Kalamata olives 
3-4 mini bell peppers sliced 
1/3 cup marinated artichoke hearts

1 teaspoon salt

Cook tortellini according to package. Drain and place in a bowl.  While still warm toss with some of the Garlic Expressions Dressing. Add in all veggies, feta cheese and seasonings.  Toss together and add more dressing. I usually use almost the entire bottle!  Serve room temperature and enjoy!

Let’s Make Shaved Brussels Sprouts and Bacon Salad!  This salad is only 4 ingredients and the dressing is only 2 simple ingredients.  It’s so light and bright and delicious!  It’s highly addictive and hard to stop eating-  the saltiness of the Parmesan cheese, paired with the savory bacon, crunchy nuts and Brussels tossed with a Lemon Vinaigrette is the perfect combo!  Recipe below and also the n my blog link in bio! #masoneats #brusselsprouts #salad

S H A V E D  B R U S S E L S + B A C O N  S A L A D 

1 bag Brussels sprouts, washed and shredded 

10 pieces of cooked bacon crumbled 

1/2 cup sliced almonds 

Fresh Parmesan Cheese 

2/3 cup olive olil

juice of 3 lemons 

1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper 

Slice or shred the Brussels Sprouts and place in a bowl.  Meanwhile heat about a tablespoon olive oil in a small pan.  Add in almonds and a little salt.  Cook on medium heat about 5-7 minutes until they are slightly brown- be careful they can burn quickly so keep an eye on them.  Add the almonds to the Brussels sprouts.  Crumble the bacon slices and add in bowl as well.  Top all with about 1/3 cup freshly grated Parmesan Cheese.  To make the dressing simple whisk or shake together the olive oil, lemon juice and salt and pepper.  Drizzle over salad and toss all together!

Let’s make Mozzarella Stuffed Chicken Meatballs! I first posted this recipe 9 years ago and have been making it ever since!  These meatballs are soooo good! The cheesy middle takes them to the next level!  This is a family favorite dinner! Recipe below and also on my blog link in bio! #masoneats #meatballs 

MOZZARELLA STUFFED CHICKEN MEATBALLS 

1 pound ground chicken
1/2 cup grated parmesan
1/3 cup panko breadcrumbs
2 eggs
3/4 teaspoon salt
3/4 teaspoon freshly cracked black pepper
1/2 teaspoon oregano
1/2 teaspoon parsley
1/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes
1/2 cups flour
bocconcini mozzarella balls
1/2 cup olive oil
1 jar tomato sauce
10 basil leaves chopped 

In
a large mixing bowl, combine the chicken, parmesan, breadcrumbs, eggs,
salt, pepper, oregano, parsley and red pepper flakes. Carefully combine
everything with your hands until the ingredients are evenly mixed.
Form the ground chicken mixture into small meatballs, each the size of a golf ball.
Insert
a small bocconcini ball in the center of each meatball, taking care to
reform the meatball around the cheese once it’s been inserted. The
mozzarella should be completely hidden from sight.
Dredge each meatball in the flour to lightly coat it and gently tap off any excess flour.
Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.
Heat
the olive oil in a large heavy bottom skillet over medium high heat.
Once the oil is hot, add half of the meatballs and sauté for a 3-4
minutes, turning every so often to brown the outside.
Once the meatballs are browned, remove them from the oil and repeat the process with the remaining meatballs.
Once all meatballs are browned, add the tomato sauce to the skillet and place the browned meatballs on top of the sauce.
Transfer
the skillet, meatballs and all, into the oven and let the meatballs
continue to bake for 10-15 minutes until cooked through.
Remove
the skillet from the oven and dusting with salt, pepper, freshly
chopped basil and extra bocconcini if desired. Serve immediately.

Over the weekend I had a butter bean soup at a restaurant and I wanted to recreate my own version!  This is filled with butter beans, Brussels sprouts, kale and andouille sausage!  The perfect chilly night cozy dinner! Recipe below and also on my blog! #masoneats #homemadesoup 

BUTTERBEAN + BRUSSELS SOUP

3 tablespoons butter
3 celery stalks diced 
3 garlic cloves minced 
1 bunch green onions sliced 
8 cups chicken or veggie broth 
2 cups butter beans (frozen or canned work)
10 Brussels Sprouts shredded finely 
1 small head kale chopped
3-4 andouille sausages chopped 
1 teaspoon salt and pepper
1/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes 
1 teaspoon Trader Joe’s Green Goddess Seasoning 
2 tablespoons grated Parmesan
2 tablespoon verde hot sauce 

In a large Dutch oven melt the butter and add in celery, minced garlic and green onions.  Cook about 5 minutes then add in shaved Brussels sprouts and cook a few minutes.  Add in 8 cups broth, butter beans, kale, sausage, salt and pepper, red pepper flakes, green goddess seasoning and let simmer about 45 minutes to an hour. Then add in Parmesan and verde hot sauce.  I will say this gets better the longer it cooks I ended up cooking ours prob 3 hours.  Scoop into bowls and serve with more Parmesan Cheese and crispy bread!

KIMCHI  CAULIFLOWER  RICE 
1 bag riced cauliflower 
1 bunch of kale destemmed and shredded 
1 bunch green onions sliced 
1 tablespoons sesame oil 
3 tablespoons soy sauce 
3-4 heaping tablespoons kimchi

CHICKEN + WILD RICE + ARTICHOKE CASSEROLE

1 cup shredded chicken (I used a rotisserie)
1 pound sausage cooked and drained 
1 small onion diced
1 small can sliced mushrooms 
1 can diced water chestnuts 
1 cup marinated artichoke hearts chopped 
1 cup spinach 
2 cups shredded sharp cheddar cheese 
1 can cream of celery soup 
2/3 cup mayo 
2/3 cup sour cream 
1 teaspoon salt 
1 teaspoon pepper 
1 tablespoon hot sauce 

Mix cream of celery soup, mayo, sour cream, salt, pepper and hot sauce in a bowl. 

Cook sausage and drain on paper towels.  In that same pan add olive oil, diced onion, mushrooms and water chestnuts.  Sauté about 5-7 minutes. 

In a large baking dish add wild rice, chicken, sausage, artichoke hearts, spinach, onions + mushrooms and cheddar cheese.  Pour sauce over top and stir all together.  Bake at 350 degrees 45 minutes

Let’s make Caesar Salad with Crispy Chickpeas + Quinoa.  This is a fun spin on Caesar Salad adding in quinoa and crispy flavored chickpeas with a lovely Lemon Tahini Dressing.  I could literally drink this dressing it’s so good!  The quinoa makes this salad heartier and the crispy chick peas add crunch and flavor.  Give it a try! #masoneats #caesarsalad 

CAESAR SALAD + CRISPY CHICKPEAS and QUINOA

1 head romaine lettuce shredded 
1 can chickpeas drained and rinsed 
1 cup cooked quinoa 
1/4 cup pine nuts 
1/2 cup freshly grated Parmesan Cheese 
1-2 tablespoons olive oil 
1/2 teaspoon salt 
1/2 teaspoon pepper 
1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
1/2 teaspoon chili powder 

DRESSING 
1/2 cup olive oil 
1/2 cup tahini
1/4 cup lemon juice 
1 garlic clove minced 
1/2 cup grated Parmesan Cheese
2 teaspoons Worcestershire
1 tablespoon Dijon 
1/2 teaspoon salt
1/2 teaspoon pepper 

Lay drained chickpeas on a baking dish and drizzle with olive oil.  Then toss with salt, pepper, garlic powder and chili powder.  Bake at 350 degrees 25 minutes.  Remove and set aside. 
In a bowl add romaine, quinoa, crispy chickpeas, pine nuts and Parmesan cheese. 

Blend together dressing ingredients.  Pour over salad and add a little more Parmesan cheese.

Let’s make Roasted Summer Squash Pasta Salad!  This is a great way to use up Summer Squash!  Roasting it gives it such a deep complex flavor. 1 bunch scallions sliced 
1 box pasta I did Gemelli 
1/2 cup sunflowers seeds 
1 cup fresh basil shredded 
3/4 cup freshly grated Parmesan cheese

Let’s make my Dad’s breakfast burritos.  These are a family favorite and a tradition on beach vacation.  My dad usually gets up before all of us and makes these, he wraps them in foil and keeps them in the oven on warm until we get up. I have tried to make these before and mine are never as good as his.  They are so delicious!  Also my dad is the best chopper ever- take a look at how finely diced the bell pepper and onion are! Recipe below and also on my blog link in bio! #masoneats #breakfastburrito 

DAD’S BREAKFAST BURRITOS 

1 package Tortillas, fajita size
12-14 Eggs
2-3 tbsp Milk
1 package Sausage (We used Jimmy Dean)
1 cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
American Cheese (any sliced cheese works)
1 small Onion, diced
1 small Green Bell Pepper and red bell oeoper, diced

Instructions
In a skillet sauté onions and bell pepper for about 5-7 minutes. Remove from pan. Use the same pan to cook the sausage. Then add in the cooked onions and peppers with the sausage. Drain on top of paper towel to remove extra grease.
In a large bowl mix 12-14 eggs with salt and pepper and a little milk. Stir in grated cheddar cheese. Mix well.
Add eggs to skillet and cook until cooked through. Once cooked stir in sausage mixture.
In a skillet heat a little butter. Place one tortilla shell in skillet and top with two pieces of American cheese and slightly melt. Remove shell and fill with egg-sausage mixture, wrap and then roll in foil. Repeat this step until all eggs are gone.

Let’s make Marinated Summer Veggie Salad.  This is a great way to clean out your fridge and use up any random veggies you have.  The beauty of this recipe is it gets better the longer it sits as the flavors mesh and the veggies soak in the marinade.  It’s all raw veggies so no cooking required.  It’s crunchy, flavorful and filling!  Recipe below and also on my website link in bio! 

MARINATED  SUMMER  VEGGIE  SALAD 

Half a head cauliflower chopped 
1 crown broccoli chopped 
1 small zucchini halved and sliced 
1 small squash halved and sliced 
1/2 red onion diced 
1/2 green bell pepper diced 
1 cup halved cherry tomatoes 
1/3 cup roasted pine nuts 
Parsley 

DRESSING 
1/2 cup olive oil 
Juice of 2 lemons
2 garlic cloves minced 
1.5 tablespoons Dijon 
4 tablespoons apple cider vinegar 
1 teaspoon salt
1 teaspoon pepper

When I first saw this @nytcooking recipe for Pizza Salad I immediately saved it because salad and pizza are two of my favorite foods ever.  The crispy pepperoni breadcrumb topping is everything!  And the dressing is almost like a light tangy Tomato vinaigrette.  The flavors are incredible! If you want to save time I would make the pepperoni breadcrumb mixture ahead of time and just store it at room temperature. 

PIZZA SALAD 

4 tablespoons olive oil 
2 ounces pepperoni slices, cut into thin strips
3/4 cup Panko breadcrumbs 
1 teaspoon garlic powder 
1 teaspoon dried oregano 
Salt, pepper, red pepper flakes 
1 tomato 
1 tablespoon pepperoncini brine 
1 large head romaine chopped m
1/3 cup sliced pepperoncinis 
1/3 cup sliced olives (I did black and green) 
1/4 red onion thinly sliced 
4 ounces fresh mozzarella 

In a medium nonstick skillet, add 2 tablespoons olive oil and the pepperoni and place over medium heat. Cook, stirring frequently, until the pepperoni is rendered and crisp, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat and use a slotted spoon to transfer the pepperoni to a plate lined with a paper towel . 

Return the skillet with leftover pepperoni oil to medium-low heat. Add the bread crumbs and cook, stirring frequently, until browned and toasty, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add the garlic powder and oregano.  Add the pepperoni strips and stir until evenly combined. Season with salt and red-pepper flakes to taste.

On a box grater, grate the tomato into a large bowl, discarding the remaining skin. Whisk in the pepperoncini brine and the remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil. Add salt, pepper and more brine to taste.  Add the romaine, pepperoncini, olives, onion and fresh mozzarella.  Top with pepperoni bread crumb mixture and toss to combine.

If you are looking for an amazing holiday appetizer you have to try my Brussels Sprouts Crostini!  This is basically a version of my favorite Brussels Sprouts salad piled high on a toasted crusty baguette.  The combination of the goat cheese spread and Brussels mixture is so lovely. BRUSSELS  SPROUTS  CROSTINI 

1 bag Brussels Sprouts, wash and shredded 
1/2 cup shredded Parmesan Cheese
1 Baguette 
1 small log goat cheese 
1/4 cup olive oil 
Juice of 2 small lemons 
1 garlic clove minced 
1 teaspoon Dijon mustard 
1/2 teaspoon salt
1/2 teaspoon pepper
1/3 cup silvered almonds 

Place the shredded Brussels Sprouts in a bowl. 

Slice the baguette and drizzle with olive oil and spicy sea salt (salt and pepper work just fine too) Bake at 350 10 mins until slightly crispy

In a small skillet add a splash of olive oil and sliced almonds.  Sprinkle with sea salt.  Cook on low heat just until slightly browned. Lay on paper towel to dry and absorb extra oil. 

Take one crostini slice and spread with goat cheese, top with a scoop of Brussels Sprouts and sprinkle with sliced almonds!

I was thrilled with this gumbo recipe! I found this in Southern Living Magazine and made a few adaptations.  This recipe is simple but a little time consuming as you need to let it simmer for about 2 hours and be around to stir it.  So pour a glass of wine and enjoy the cooking!  Perfect weekend meal!  I think because it simmers for so long the flavor is so incredible!  Recipe below! #masoneats #gumbo 

GUMBO 

1 cup canola oil 
1 cup all purpose flour 
1.5 lbs andouille sausage sliced 
1 large onion diced 
1 large green bell pepper diced 
4 celery stalks diced 
6 garlic cloves minced 
8 cups chicken stock 
2 tsp salt 
2 tsp dried thyme 
1/4-1/2 tsp dried cayenne pepper 
3 Bay Leaves 
1 lbs frozen okra 
1.5 lbs peeled and deveined shrimp 
Cooked white rice 
I added in 2 teaspoons hot sauce 
1 teaspoon creole seasoning 

Stir together oil and flour in Dutch oven.  Cook over medium low heat stirring  frequently until they mixture turns the color of chocolate milk - about an hour 

While roux cooks, cook andouille sausage in 2 batches on skillet.  After cooked remove and add olive oil.  Add in onions, bell pepper, and celery.  Cook about 8-10 minutes until veggies soften.  Stir in garlic and cook about 3 minutes and remove from heat. 

Stir veggie mixture into cooked roux. Add in chicken stock whisking constantly.  Stir in salt, thyme, cayenne pepper, bay leaves and andouille sausage.  Bring to a boil and then reduce heat to medium low and simmer uncovered for an hour.  Stir occasionally. 

Stir frozen okra into stock and cook for 15 minutes.  Stir in shrimp and cook about another 10 minutes.  Serve over white rice!

Place 3 cups arugula, 2 chopped scallions, basil, cottage cheese, lemon juice, Parmesan cheese, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper in food processor.  Blend well, scoop sides down and add in 2 tablespoons olive oil and blend again. 

Toss cooked pasta with arugula pesto.  Add in a handful of arugula and roasted broccoli and lightly toss.  Top with freshly grated Parmesan cheese, red pepper flakes and a drizzle of olive oil.
